<subSubSection id="A8C015289C0F6E17CEEAD9DF0B1DE008" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="BAA346807528315980716A1FC36B009C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="44EECB1BE94914857A7D4F735E1A3A20" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName id="E2D0EFF6F7F0BAF5599024DA568E65BB" authorityName="Z. F. Yu, M. Qiao &amp; R. F. Castaneda" authorityYear="2021" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="Isthmomyces" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Isthmomyces macrosporus" order="Microthyriales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="macrosporus">
<emphasis id="92C5D262C0466CA321E0D0B82260EB72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Isthmomyces macrosporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is close to 
<taxonomicName id="7EE4924DF69376990A2B43877C37273A" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="I." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="I. dissimilis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="dissimilis">
<emphasis id="2554454C37753CC92323FF778A01EC9D" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. dissimilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="54C674CB7F08DC00901136CE7F50982C" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="I." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="I. lanceatus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="lanceatus">
<emphasis id="AA44E053CB47DFBB5EC7B31A66125807" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. lanceatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, 
<taxonomicName id="161E2B3B141A8401581198F05F8F0F24" class="Dothideomycetes" family="Microthyriaceae" genus="I." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="I. macrosporus" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="macrosporus">
<emphasis id="29254A23E90491DAF2C9FE60D10CFE55" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">I. macrosporus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is different from all species within this genus by having larger conidia, obviously brown conidiophores and few denticulate conidiogenous cells (Hoog and Hennebert 1983).
</paragraph>
